- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper focuses on the design automation of adiabatic circuits, which falls under the hardware architecture category. 
- cs.EM (Electromagnetics): Adiabatic circuits are designed to minimize energy dissipation, which is related to the electromagnetic properties of the circuit. 
- cs.DC (Digital Circuits): Adiabatic circuits are a type of digital circuit, and the paper discusses their design automation. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper discusses the switching rules that are different from conventional circuitry, which is related to the logic in computer science.
